---
{
	layout: "layouts/base"
}
---

<section id="intro">
	<div class="content bordered">

		<div>
			<div class="status"><span></span>Available for work</div>
		</div>

		<div class="who-am-i">
			<div class="header-content">
				<div class="heading-and-title">
					<h1 class="main-heading">I'm Aubrey.</h1>
					<p class="title">Web Developer / Designer</p>
				</div>

				{{ "I _build and maintain_ websites for people who are **sick of doing it themselves** who wish they had someone **on their team** to take care of it." | markdown | safe }}
			</div>

			<img src="/assets/img/aubrey.jpg" alt="Aubrey Portwood" onload="setTimeout( () => this.classList.add( 'loaded' ), 1000 )">
		</div>

		<ol class="you-run-your-business">
			<li>You run your business.</li>
			<li>I'll run the website.</li>
		</ol>

		<p><a href="#" class="button alt1" data-koalendar="true">Book free kickoff call <span class="material-symbols-outlined">calendar_add_on</span></a></p>
	</div>
</section>

<section id="how" class="textured">
	<div class="content bordered">

		<h2>How it works</h2>

		<h3>We build a website.</h3>

		<div class="content-block">
			{{ "Unless you already have a website, we build a website that's _**directly aligned with your business's goals.**_ They're **lean**, **simple**, and _**you own it.**_ End our relationship? **Your website stays up.**" | markdown | safe }}

			<p>
				<a href="#" class="button">Learn more <span class="desktop">about how I build websites</span><span class="material-symbols-outlined">open_in_new</span></a>
			</p>
		</div>

		<h3>Now, consider me a part of <strong>your team.</strong></h3>

		<div class="content-block">
			{{ "**Need content updates?** Want to run a campaign? _Not sure?_" | markdown | safe }}
			{{ "I work directly with you _**every month**_ to make sure you are getting the most out of your website. Whatever's going on, **I make sure your website is working along-side your what your business is doing.**" | markdown | safe }}
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<section id="reviews" class="white">
	<div class="content full no-gap">
		<ul class="testimonials">
			{% for review in reviews %}
				<li>
					<span class="icon">&rdquo;</span>
					<span class="quote">&ldquo;{{ review.quote }}&rdquo;</span>
					<div class="name-and-company">
						<span class="name">{{ review.name }}</span>
						<span class="company">{{ review.company }}</span>
					</div>
				</li>
			{% endfor %}
		</ul>
	</div>
</section>

<section id="experience">
	<div class="content bordered centered">

		<h2>I've spent over a <em class="emu"><strong>decade</strong></em> building websites with agencies who focused on enterprise sized companies.</h2>

		<div class="progress">
			<div class="am">
				<h3 class="years">3 years</h3>
				<div class="where">AwesomeMotive</div>
			</div>
			<div class="webdev">
				<h3 class="years">7 years</h3>
				<div class="where">WebDevStudios</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<p class="claim">Now I use that experience to help people <strong>get more out of thier website.</strong></p>
	</div>
</section>

<section id="cta" class="textured">
	<div class="content bordered centered">
		<h2>Ready for a <em>new</em> website experience?</h2>
		<p><a href="#" class="button alt1 big" data-koalendar="true">Book free kickoff call <span class="material-symbols-outlined">calendar_add_on</span></a></p>
	</div>
</section>
